Looking at the code fragments, I can see that Hexi provides a `binary_stream` class that works with a `buffer_adaptor` to read from binary buffers. The `read_container` method is used to read collections of items.

Here's the implementation for the `read_item_batch` function:

```cpp
#include <hexi/hexi.h>
#include <vector>
#include <cstdint>
#include <span>

std::vector<uint32_t> read_item_batch(const std::span<const uint8_t> buffer) {
    // Create a buffer adaptor from the input span
    hexi::buffer_adaptor adaptor(buffer);

    // Create a binary stream from the adaptor
    hexi::binary_stream stream(adaptor);

    // Read the item count (uint32_t)
    uint32_t item_count;
    stream >> item_count;

    // Use read_container to read all items into a vector
    std::vector<uint32_t> items;
    stream.read_container(items, item_count);

    return items;
}
```

